<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   DPRK Reportedly Sent Task Force to PRC </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Reportedly Sent Task Force to PRC </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1704233994 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 2210 GMT 17 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1704233994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Yi Tong-sik from Beijing] </F>
  [Text] A Beijing-based source said that North Korea had 
sent a special task force to Beijing during President Kim 
Yong-sam's visit to China. The task force was made up of 
responsible North Korean high-level working officials from 
various sectors -- such as politics, international affairs, and 
economics -- and arrived in Beijing two days before President 
Kim Yong-sam's visit and collected information regarding the 
contents of the ROK-PRC talks, including the summit talks 
between Presidents Kim Yong-sam and Jiang Zemin, and the future 
development of their talks. 
  The source stated that through the task force, in 
particular, 
North Korea prudently focused on China's position regarding the 
nuclear issue and observed how the ROK-PRC talks could affect 
the United States or the United Nations. 

</TEXT>

