<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iraqi Foreign Minister Continues Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraqi Foreign Minister Continues Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With Foreign Minister Alatas </H4>

<F P=102> JN1804200094 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in 
Arabic 1800 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1804200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [Iraqi] Foreign Minister Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf, 
President Saddam Husayn's envoy to Indonesian President Suharto, 
met in Jakarta today with Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali 
Alatas. Al- Sahhaf briefed his Indonesian counterpart on the 
status of the relations between Iraq and the United Nations 
regarding the implementation of UN Security Council resolutions, 
especially Resolution 687. He stressed that a clear majority 
has emerged at the UN Security Council calling for dealing with 
Iraq in light of the implementation of the resolutions. This is 
in order to set a clear timetable for closing the file of Part C 
of Resolution 687, which would mean that the UN Security Council 
should immediately start implementation of Paragraph 22 of the 
resolution, allowing Iraq to export its products abroad. 
  The foreign minister also briefed the Indonesian side on the 
recent National Assembly speaker's statement on Iraq's readiness 
to receive a Kuwaiti parliamentary delegation. 
  Ali Alatas expressed understanding of Iraq's position. The 
two sides discussed bilateral cooperation and coordination 
within the Nonaligned Movement. They also discussed ways of 
bolstering bilateral relations in the interest of both countries. 
  Foreign Minister Muhammad Sa'id al-Sahhaf, leader President 
Saddam Husayn's envoy to Indonesian President Suharto, arrived 
in Jakarta yesterday 

</TEXT>

