<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Remarks on Situation in Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Remarks on Situation in Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1804154594 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1500 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1804154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Ali Altas said that Indonesia is 
worried about the indecisive attitude shown by the United 
Nations and NATO toward the Serbs in Gorazde, Bosnia. He said 
that the United Nations had declared Gorazde a safe haven and 
that no party could interfere there. Therefore, according to 
the resolution, the United Nations and NATO should take firm 
action against the Serbs for violating the United Nations 
resolution several times. 
  Foreign Minister Ali Alatas said that the Foreign Affairs 
Department is continuously monitoring the situation in Gorazde 
and is making efforts to seek the release of five Indonesian 
military observers taken hostage by the Serbs. He said the 
worrying situation in Bosnia does not change Indonesia's wish to 
send health officials or other military observers to Bosnia. 

</TEXT>

