<F P=102>   SK1904053994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0425 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1904053994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 19 (KCNA) -- Greenpeace, the 
international organisation of environmental movement, urged the 
puppet authorities of South Korea to stop the construction 
project of the atomic power station now underway, according to a 
radio report from Seoul. 
  Some 20 members of the organisation raised this demand at an 
anti-nuke rally they held in Samchok on April 14 with about 
1,000 members of environmental protection and anti-nuke 
organisations of South Korea. 
  Sounding a warning against the danger of radioactive leakage 
from the South Korean atomic power station, Greenpeace is 
strongly demanding a stop to its construction project, said the 
radio. 

</TEXT>

