<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Supports National Conference Plan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon Supports National Conference Plan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1804152294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1507 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1804152294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang April (KCNA) -- A meeting of 
representatives of the General Association of Korean Residents 
in Japan (Chongnyon) and its organizations supporting the 
convocation of a national conference proposed at a joint meeting 
of the government, political parties and social organizations of 
the DPRK was held in Tokyo on April 13. 
  The joint meeting held on April 11 proposed to the South 
Korean authorities, political parties, organisations and 
individual figures and overseas Koreans to hold a national 
conference in Pyongyang or Seoul on the occasion of August 15. 
  So Man-sol, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee 
of Chongnyon, in his report at the meeting said the proposal is 
fair and feasible one acceptable to anyone either in view of the 
time or in view of its content. 
  The proposal of the joint meeting for convening a national 
conference enables all Koreans who want national reunification 
to unite as one nation, transcending the difference in idea, 
ideology and system, no matter where they live and what they do, 
and enables not only the authorities but also the compatriots of 
all walks of life in the North and South and overseas to take 
full responsibility for the reunification of the country, he 
said. 
  He strongly demanded that the South Korean authorities 
renounce confrontation and nuclear war exercises and actively 
respond to creating a favorable atmosphere for convening a 
national conference from the stand of great unity of the nation. 
  He called for waging as an all-compatriotic movement the 
struggle to bring to a success the convocation of a national 
conference proposed at the joint meeting. 
  A statement supporting the convocation of a national 
conference was adopted at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

