<H3> <TI>   Irish Party Delegation, WPK Meet for Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Irish Party Delegation, WPK Meet for Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Party Delegates Exchange Views </H4>

<F P=102> SK1304213694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1507 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1304213694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 13 (KCNA) -- Talks between the 
delegations of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] and the 
Workers' Party of Ireland [WPI] were held here today. 
  Present at the talks on the Korean side were Hwang 
Chang-yop, 
secretary; Kim Yang-kon, vice department director, of the C.C. 
[Central Committee], the WPK; officials concerned, and on the 
opposite side were the members of the delegation headed by 
General Secretary of the WPI Pat Quearney. 
  The sides informed each other of activities of their parties 
and exchanged views on the development of friendly relations 
between the two parties and some other matters of common concern. 
  The talks proceeded in a friendly atmosphere. 

</TEXT>

