and the visiting chairman of the Ireland-Korea Friendship 
Association took place in Pyongyang on April 18. 
  Present there were Sean Garland, chairman of the 
Ireland-Korea Friendship Association, and Pat Quearney, general 
secretary of the Workers' Party of Ireland. 
  Kim Yong-nam, vice-chairman of the Central Committee of the 
General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea and chairman of the 
Korea-Ireland Friendship Association, and officials concerned 
were present. 
  The participants had a conversation in a friendly 
atmosphere. 

