<H3> <TI>   Special Envoy of Libyan President Visits Capital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Special Envoy of Libyan President Visits Capital </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Arrives at Airport </H4>

<F P=102> SK1804054194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0519 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1804054194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 18 (KCNA) -- The inspector-general 
of the Armed Forces of Libya, Mustafa al Haroubi, who is a 
special envoy of the leader of the great September First 
revolution of the Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab 
Jamahiriya, and his entourage arrived here Sunday. They were met 
at the airport by Choe Kwang, chief of the General Staff of the 
Korean People's Army, Chang Song-kil, vice-minister of Foreign 
Affairs, officials concerned and Ramadan Muhammad El Laubi, 
acting secretary of the People's Committee of the Libyan 
People's Bureau in Korea. 
  A ceremony for welcoming the special envoy and his entourage 
took place at the airport. 
  In the evening, the government of the Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea gave a party for the special envoy and his 
entourage at the Mansudae Assembly Hall. 

</TEXT>

