<H3> <TI>   Special Envoy of Libyan President Visits Capital </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Special Envoy of Libyan President Visits Capital </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kim Il-song Receives Envoy </H4>

<F P=102> SK1904115794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1103 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1904115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 19 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song on April 19 received the inspector-general 
of Armed Forces of Libya, Mustafa al-Haroubi, who is a special 
envoy of the leader of the great September first revolution of 
the great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya and his 
entourage on a visit to Korea. 
  Present there were Vice-premier and Foreign Minister Kim 
Yong- nam, chief of the General Staff of the Korean People's 
Army Choe Kwang, Vice-minister of Foreign Affairs Chang Song-kil 
and acting Secretary of the People's Committee of the Libyan 
People's Bureau in Korea Ramadan Muhammad al-Ra'Ubi. 
  The special envoy warmly congratulated President Kim Il-song 
on his birthday, wishing him good health and a long life, and 
conveyed to him a personnel letter of His Excellency Mu'ammar 
al-Qadhdhafi, leader of the great September first revolution of 
the great Socialist People's Libyan Abab Jamahiriya. 
  Expressing thanks for them President Kim Il-song conversed 
with the guests in a cordial and friendly atmosphere. 
  President Kim Il-song arranged a luncheon for the guests. 

</TEXT>

