<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Former Heads of State Continue Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Former Heads of State Continue Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    View West Sea Barrage </H4>

<F P=102> SK1604044294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0423 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1604044294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- The Pyongyang-visiting 
group of former heads of state and government and politicians of 
different countries led by ex-president of Costa Rica Rodrigo 
Carazo Odio staying in Korea visited the West Sea barrage Friday. 
  The barrage with a 8 km dam across a rough sea tens of 
metres 
deep was built by soldier builders in a matter of 5 years. 
  The head of the visiting-group had this to say: 
  "The West Sea barrage is a monumental edifice for the 
prosperity of the country and the welfare of the people. 
  "The excellent monumental creation can be built only when 
wise guidance, mass strength and technical wisdom are combined. 
I think it is very beneficial for visitors to Korea to see this 
monument. It is because the only people who aspire after peace, 
progress and prosperity can create such a great and magnificent 
monument. It is a creation which serves peace and the promotion 
of people's living." 
  He expressed thanks to the government and people of Korea 
who 
have built the excellent monument showing the massive will and 
strength and leadership as a whole. Executive Director of the 
Summit Council for World Peace Antonio Betancourt wrote in 
visitor's book that the barrage is a great creation showing the 
ardent love of the Korean people for their leader, their country 
and future. 
  On the same day, the visiting group was ushered to the 
recreation ground on Mt. Taesong, where the group spent a 
pleasant time of rest with working people in Pyongyang enjoying 
the April holiday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

