<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Former Heads of State Continue Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Former Heads of State Continue Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Canada's Schreyer Comments </H4>

<F P=102> SK1804111494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1024 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1804111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 18 (KCNA) -- Former 
Governor-General of Canada Edward Schreyer on a visit to Korea 
told a press conference here on April 15 that the reports of the 
West about Korea were distorted and the impressions he got from 
his current visit were so deep that they were beyond wordy 
description. 
  "What I have seen in your country is quite different from 
what I have heard through the Western media," he said, and 
continued: 
  "While staying in your country, I have been deeply impressed 
by the fact that the Korean people live with smiles and enjoy 
happiness to the full unlike what I have heard in the West. 
  "Your people live with their own aim and have successfully 
built their country with industrious and creative activities. 
  "The grand and beautiful architectures built by your people 
made me think a great deal. 
  "The wonderful architectures are rich in content and 
peculiar 
in architectural beauty, to say nothing of the external style. 
  "We do not want the outbreak of a war in your country but 
hope that the Korean people will live in peace" 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

