<H3> <TI>   Foreign Former Heads of State Continue Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Former Heads of State Continue Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Visitors Tour Capital </H4>

<F P=102> SK1904074794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0443 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1904074794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 19 (KCNA) -- A Pyongyang-visiting 
group of former heads of state and government and politicians of 
different countries led by ex-President of Costa Rica Rodrigo 
Carazo Odio, staying in Korea, visited the Mansudae Art Studio 
on April 18. 
  They saw wonderful porcelains, embroidery articles, 
engravings and Korean paintings created under the wise guidance 
of the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  At the end of the visit, the head of the group wrote in the 
visitor's book that the studio is a comprehensive creative base 
showing how excellent the Korean art and fine arts are. 
  Former Prime Minister of Egypt Aziz Sedky said all the works 
of the studio fully show the Korean art which is very excellent 
and charming. 
  The group visited the Pyongyang metro. 
  After the visit Mark P. Barry, director of Research of the 
Summit Council for World Peace, said this metro is the most 
beautiful, excellent and clean in the world. 
  Noting that the world knows little about this, he said he 
was 
pleased to hear that the metro would be extended in the future. 
  He expressed the belief that it would be not a long time 
before the whole world come to know what a developed country 
Korea is. 
  Earlier, the guests visited the Tower of the Chuche Idea and 
the Korean Central History Museum. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

