<H3> <TI>   Foreign Former Heads of State Continue Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Former Heads of State Continue Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kim Yong-sun Hosts Banquet </H4>

<F P=102> SK1904071894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0448 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1904071894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 19 (KCNA) -- A banquet was given in 
Pyongyang on the evening of April 18 for the Pyongyang-visiting 
group of former heads of state and government and politicians of 
different countries on a visit to Korea. 
  Invited there were head of the group Rodrigo Carazo Odio, 
ex-president of Costa Rica, and members of the group, former 
Governor-General of Canada Edward Schreyer, former Prime 
Minister of Egypt Aziz Sedky, former member of the Parliament of 
France and member of the European Parliament Pierro Ceyrac, 
senior vice-president of the Center for Strategic and 
International Studies of the United States William Taylor, 
senior vice-president of the CNN International Eason Jordan, 
executive director of the Summit Council for World Peace Antonio 
Betancourt, director of research of the Summit Council for World 
Peace Mark P. Barry, former Senior Advisor to the Assistant 
Secretary of State for Human Rights of the United States James 
Zumwalt, Managing Editor of the WASHINGTON TIMES Josette Shiner, 
Executive Director of the WASHINGTON TIMES Photo Agency Victoria 
Yokota, President Hirogatsu Ota and Vice-President Togashi 
Takayoshi of the Summit Council for World Strategy of Japan, and 
other members and journalists accompanying them. 
  Kim Yong-sun, secretary of the Central Committee of the 
Workers' Party of Korea, and head of the group Rodrigo Carazo 
Odio made speeches at the banquet. 

</TEXT>

