<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Party Delegations Wrap Up Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Party Delegations Wrap Up Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kang Song-san Speaks at Banquet </H4>

<F P=102> SK1604044594 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2200 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1604044594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 2200 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Speech by Kang Song-san, member of the Political Bureau of </F>
the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK) and 
premier of the Administration Council, at a banquet arranged by 
DPRK President Kim Il-song at the Kumsusan Assembly Hall for the 
foreign delegations and delegations of overseas Koreans on 15 
April -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] Comrades and respected foreign guests: 
  Today, all the people across the nation, with infinite joy 
and a sense of boundless admiration, are grandly celebrating the 
great leader's birthday as the greatest auspicious holiday of 
the nation. We feel it an utmost honor and joy to be in the 
presence of high-level delegations and goodwill missions of 
various countries, and delegations of overseas compatriots with 
the respected and beloved leader Comrade Kim Il-song in 
attendance. 
  Authorized by the great leader Comrade Kim Il-song, and on 
behalf of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] Central Committee 
and the government of the republic, I warmly welcome and extend 
my deep thanks to the foreign party delegations, foreign 
goodwill missions, and friends who are here in our country to 
join in the joy of our people on the occasion of our nation's 
auspicious April holiday. In addition, I warmly welcome and 
give fervent fraternal greetings to the congratulatory 
delegations and figures of overseas compatriots from different 
regions and organizations who came here to deliver unanimous 
greetings from overseas compatriots to the great leader. 
  Since he embarked on the road of revoluion, the respected 
leader Comrade Kim Il-song has victoriously led the Korean 
revolution with his outstanding and tested leadership and 
tireless efforts of devotion for a long time. In doing so, he 
performed immortal exploits for the country, the revolution, the 
times, and history. 
  Even today, the great leader Comrade Kim Il-song -- with 
extraordinary wisdom, excelled leadership, and lofty popular 
traits -- is vigorously leading our people's struggle for 
socialist construction and the national reunification on a 
correct road of victory, and is directing big efforts for the 
country's ever-lasting prosperity. 
  Thanks to the respected and beloved Comrade Kim Il-song's 
outstanding and tested leadership, our people are powerfully 
demonstrating the superiority of the popular mass-centered 
socialism of our own style; are effecting a constant upswing in 
socialist construction; and are valiantly advancing toward the 
denuclearization of the Korean peninsula and the independent and 
peaceful reunification of the country without the slightest 
vacillation under the complex and difficult conditions created 
by the continued challenges and obstructions by the imperialists 
and reactionaries. 
  Independence, peace, and friendship are basic doctrines in 
the foreign policy our party and republic's government have 
consistently carried through. 
  Our party and republic's government, as in the past, will 
invariably and consistently implement the foreign policy of 
independence, peace and friendship, and thus actively contribute 
to the peace and progress of mankind and the world's cause of 
independence. 
  At this meaningful place filled with a sense of boundless 
admiration and warm friendship for the great leader, I propose a 
toast to our fatherland's everlasting prosperity, to our 
nation's eternal happiness, to national reunification, and to 
the completion of the chuche revolutionary cause. 
  I also propose a toast to the long life and good health of 
Comrade Kim Il-song, the great leader of our party and people, 
who is observing the 82d anniversary of his birth; to the health 
of delegations of foreign parties of various countries; and to 
the health of foreign comrades and friends who came to 
congratulate the auspicious holiday of the nation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

