<H4>    Kang Song-san, Chang Chol at Show </H4>

<F P=102> SK1404051794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0451 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1404051794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Korean cadres saw a 
circus show by acrobats from different countries participating 
in the 12th April Spring Friendship Art Festival at the 
Pyongyang Circus Theatre on Wednesday evening. 
  The show was seen by Premier Kang Song-san, Vice-premier and 
Minister of Culture and Art and Chairman of the Festival 
Organizing Committee Chang Chol, Minister of Finance Yun 
Ki-chong, Chairman of the State Commission of Physical Culture 
and Sports Pak Myong-chol, other officials concerned and working 
people and artistes in the city. 
  The performers put on stage colorful numbers including 
"aerial plastic stunt," "plastic trio," "hand feats," "the 
wedding day of a girl," "spear revolving" and "aerial flight on 
trapeze" which were acclaimed by the audience. 
  A floral basket was conveyed to the acrobats for their 
successful performance. 

</TEXT>

