<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Party Delegations Wrap Up Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Party Delegations Wrap Up Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kim Il-song Attends Performances </H4>

<F P=102> SK1804051294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0452 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1804051294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- The great leader 
President Kim Il-song saw joint performances given by artistes 
of different countries participating in the 12th April Spring 
Friendship Art Festival. 
  When he appeared in the auditorium amid the playing of the 
welcome music, stormy cheers of "hurrah!" and thunderous 
applause shook the hall. 
  The performances were seen by Kang Song-san, member of the 
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party 
of Korea [WPK] and premier of the Administration Council, and 
Yi Chong-ok, Pak Song-chol and Kim Yong-chu, Politburo members 
of the WPK Central Committee and vice-presidents, Kim Pyong-sik, 
vice-president and chairman of the Central Committee of the 
Korean Social Democratic Party, and other cadres and working 
people in the city. 
  Among the audience were Yi Chin-kyu, first vice-chairman of 
the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of 
Korean residents in Japan (Chongnyon), Choe Hong-hui, president 
of the International Taekwon-do Federation, and other Korean 
figures overseas. 
  Invited to see the performances were foreign guests on a 
visit to Korea, including Huudu Yahaya, general secretary of the 
National Democratic Congress of Ghana; P.V. Svoik, co-chairman 
of the Socialist Party of Kazakhstan; and Pat Quearney, general 
secretary of the Workers' Party of Ireland; and foreign 
diplomatic envoys here. 
  The performers included international and national concours 
prize winners of different countries and famous artistes who 
came with boundless feelings of respect for and trust in 
President Kim Il-song and warm sentiments of friendship toward 
the Korean people, and Korean artistes from overseas and at home. 
  They extended the highest glory and warmest congratulations 
to President Kim Il-song on his birthday and gave an impressive 
artistic representation of his immortal feats and greatness. 
  They also highly sang of their ardent reverence for the dear 
leader Comrade Kim Chong-il who has exalted Korea, the homeland 
of chuche, and is victoriously advancing the socialist cause 
with his clairvoyance, matchless grit and rare leadership 
ability. 
  They well showed the sacred struggle, creative labour and 
customs of different nations who have turned out to accomplish 
the cause of global independence. 
  The performances were highly acclaimed by the audience for 
their high ideological and artistic value. 
  President Kim Il-song sent floral baskets to the performers 
in congratulation of their successful performances. 
  He met foreign artists and delegations of Korean artists 
from 
overseas who had participated in the performances, and 
delegations of Chongnyon and the delegation of the Chinese 
Ministry of Culture and foreign diplomatic envoys here and posed 
for souvenir pictures with them. 

</TEXT>

