<F P=102> SK1904122494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1037 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1904122494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 19 (KCNA) -- The dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il on April 18 received a letter of thanks 
from the participants in the 12th April spring friendship art 
festival which had taken place in Pyongyang. 
  The letter says the festival was a beautiful stage of 
friendship and unity in which they loudly sang as songs of 
praise of the times the desire and aspirations of mankind to 
live happily in a free and peaceful world under the noble idea 
of independence, peace and friendship. 
  Through a visit to beautiful Korea, it goes on, we have got 
deep impressions, great confidence and inspiration from the 
indomitable spirit of the Korean people confidently advancing 
along the road of independence continuously under the banner of 
socialism, firmly united behind Your Excellency Kim Chong-il. 
  They said in the letter that during their stay in Korea they 
have come to know well that under the wise leadership of His 
Excellency Kim Chong-il the traditions of national culture and 
art are being preserved and inherited successfully and many 
literary and art works of eternal vitality and monumental 
significance have been created to stir up all the people in the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea. 
  They stressed that they would actively participate in the 
future, too, in the April spring friendship art festival under 
the noble idea of the festival and continue to beautifully 
decorate it as a great international art festival stage. 
  They wished His Excellency Kim Chong-il good health and long 
life. 

</TEXT>

