<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 16 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il-song 
of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea today sent a 
message of greetings to Hafiz al-Asad, president of the Syrian 
Arab Republic, on the occasion of the 48th anniversary of the 
independence of Syria. 
  President Kim Il-song in the message said that after the 
independence the Syrian Arab people have made great strides in 
the struggle to defend the sovereignty of the country and 
national dignity and build a new prosperous society. 
  He noted that the Korean people rejoice as over their own 
over the success made by the Syrian Arab people and always 
express firm solidarity with the efforts of the president and 
the Syrian Arab people for the independent development of the 
country and a fair and comprehensive solution of the Middle-East 
issue. 
  He expressed the belief that the excellent relations of 
friendship and cooperation existing between the two countries 
would grow stronger and develop day by day. 

</TEXT>

