<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sirivut Receives UN Secretary General's Envoy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sirivut Receives UN Secretary General's Envoy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1804131494 Phnom Penh AKP in English 1009 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1804131494 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh AKP April 18 -- Prince Kromkhun Norodom 
Sirivut, minister of foreign affairs and international 
cooperation, gave an audience to Mr. Benny Widyono, UN secretary 
general's representative, at the Foreign Ministry office. 
  During the audience, Benny Widyono informed H.R.H. [His 
Royal 
Highness] Prince Kromkhun Norodom Sirivut that he was appointed 
by the UN secretary general as his representative in Cambodian 
[as received] in accordance with the resolution 880 (1993), 
paragraph 13, adopted by the UN Security Council at its 3303rd 
meeting on 4 November 1993, with the following mandate of which 
the initial term is 6 month period: 
  -- To maintain close liaison and dialogue with the host 
government in accordance with the spirit and principle of the 
Paris agreement. 
  -- To monitor the political situation in Cambodia and 
report on significant developments relating to peace and 
security in the country. 
  -- To maintain close contact with UN chief military 
liaison officer and provide him with political guidance. 
  -- To maintain liaison and dialogue with the resident 
coordinator, the head of the human right center in Cambodia and 
other UN agencies. 
  -- To report on his activities to the secretary general 
through the under secretary general for political affairs. 
  For his part, Prince Kromkhun Norodom Sirivut has warmly 
welcomed the presence of Mr. Benny Widyono as a representative 
of the UN secretary general in Cambodian and affirmed that the 
royal government will give its full support and arrangements for 
the UN mission in Cambodia. 

</TEXT>

