<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rockets, Mortar Shells Fired on Cambodian Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rockets, Mortar Shells Fired on Cambodian Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1504020194 Bangkok BANGKOK POST in English 15 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> BK1504020194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok BANGKOK POST </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Aranyaprathet -- Thai soldiers yesterday fired eight 
mortar shells into Cambodia after five rockets believed to have 
been fired by Cambodian government gunners landed in a Thai 
village at Ban Saensuk of Tambon Khlong Namsai. 
  One rocket fell on the house of Samran Ploimali, 30, and the 
shrapnel slightly injured her daughter, Sirikanya, 12. 
  Thai gunners at first fired a smoke shell to warn Cambodian 
troops but Cambodian gunners, stationed at kilometre 4 on 
Highway No. 5, refused to heed the warning and kept on firing 
artillery, mortar and rocket-launchers at the Khmer Rouge 
stronghold at Phnum Malai with stray shells landing in Thailand, 
according to Thai sources. 
  Thai gunners then fired eight mortar shells into Cambodia. 
  It is not known whether the shells caused any casualties 
among Phnom Penh troops. 

</TEXT>

