<H3> <TI>   Panel Opposes Formation of Body To Handle PKO </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Panel Opposes Formation of Body To Handle PKO </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2004041694 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 18 Apr 94 
Evening Edition p 2--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2004041694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The "Defense Issues Forum" (with Kotaro Higuchi as 
chairman), a private advisory council to Prime Minister Morihiro 
Hosokawa, held its seventh meeting at the Prime Minister's 
Official Residence on 18 April to discuss various issues such as 
the current situation concerning UN peacekeeping operation (PKO) 
activities and the creation of a new organization to promote PKO 
participation and disarmament and arms control. As advocated by 
the Social Democratic Party of Japan [SPDJ] and other parties, 
the argument for a new organization for PKO participation 
concerns the concept of creating a new organization other than 
the Self-Defense Forces. 
  Chairman Higuchi said that in the course of the discussions, 
a majority of the panel members voiced their opposition to the 
plan. For example, one said, "When the United Nation requests 
the dispatch of military personnel, the military ranks of the 
personnel are specified." And another said: "Even if a new 
organization should be created, it would be considered by the 
international community to be a military force and its members 
to be servicemen. Therefore, it will not be efficient to take 
the trouble to create a new organization." 

</TEXT>

