<H3> <TI>   Organization Board Delegation Leaves for SRV </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Organization Board Delegation Leaves for SRV </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2104013994 Vientiane KPL in English 0750 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2104013994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, April 20 (KPL) -- A delegation of the 
Organisation Board of the Lao People's Revolutionary Party 
Central Committee led by its head Thongsing Thammavong, Party CC 
[Central Committee] Politburo member, yesterday left here for 
Hanoi on an official visit to the Socialist Republic of Vietnam. 
  The visit, which is to last ten days, was made at the 
invitation of the Organisation Board of the Communist Party of 
Vietnam Central Committee. The Lao delegation will meet with its 
Vietnamese counterpart to discuss and share experiences 
concerning organisational affairs and party cadre training at 
the new stage. 
  Seeing the delegation off at the airport were Thongsavat 
Khaikhamphithoun, Party CC member, head of the Party CC Office; 
and senior officials of the Organisation Board. Vietnamese 
Ambassador to Laos Bui Van Thanh was also present. 

</TEXT>

