acts and the campaign over "nuclear threat from the North." 
  The Arab Islamic Democratic Movement and the 
Islamic-Christian United Action Front in a letter to the U.S. 
President criticized the U.S. for reversing the agreed 
conclusions reached at the DPRK-U.S. contact in New York and 
held that the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula must be 
settled through DPRK-U.S. talks. 
