<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ukrainian Foreign Minister Makes Official Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ukrainian Foreign Minister Makes Official Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Considered `Significant Visit' </H4>

<F P=102> BK2104160394 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 21 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2104160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Station commentary] </F>
  [Text] Ukrainian Foreign Minister Anatoliy Maksymovych 
arrived in Hanoi on Thursday for an official visit to Vietnam at 
the invitation of Vietnamese Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam. 
Radio Voice of Vietnam reviews relations between Vietnam and 
Ukraine over the past years. 
  The visit to Vietnam by the Ukrainian foreign minister is of 
great significance to both countries as this is the first visit 
to Vietnam of a foreign minister from Ukraine, a republic of the 
former Soviet Union. It is a start in relations between the two 
countries. 
  Following a foreign policy to be friends with all nations in 
the world, Vietnam has established diplomatic relations with all 
the member countries of the Commonwealth of Independent States 
after the collapse of the former Soviet Union. Diplomatic 
relations with Ukraine was established in January 1992. Today, 
the bilateral relations between Vietnam and Ukraine has 
developed in many fields. The number of agreements to be signed 
by the two countries with a view to exploiting each other's 
potential will help the economic development of each country. 
They include the agreement on economic relations; trade, 
military, technical, and aviation cooperation; a protocol on 
foreigners; and an agreement on the travelling of citizens in 
each country. 
  Vietnam and Ukraine have also signed other documents such as 
the agreement on the encouragement and protection of investment; 
the agreement on the avoidance of double taxation; a consular 
agreement; and an agreement on cooperation in culture, science, 
and education. 
  Both nations are now promoting the trading ties. In 1992, 
the two-way trade turnover was only $15 million. In 1993, the 
turnover was also lightly increased. Vietnam mainly imported 
dairy products, steel, and construction materials, while Ukraine 
imported agriculture products and consumers goods. Ukraine is 
assisting Vietnam in building the Yali Hydroelectric Power Plant 
and another project with a total capital of $18 million. 
  This visit by the Ukrainian foreign minister is a good 
opportunity for the two countries to join efforts and find 
measures to further strengthen the cooperative economic 
relations. The visit is also a chance for the two countries to 
exchange experiences in economic development of each country. 
The Vietnamese people as well as the Ukrainian people hope that 
this visit to Vietnam by Minister Anatoliy Maksymovych will make 
contribution to the development of relations between the two 
countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

