<DOCNO> FBIS4-6552 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreas078_n_94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-078 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  21 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Do Muoi Holds Talks With Lao Party Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Do Muoi Holds Talks With Lao Party Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204091994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
2300 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2204091994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Hanoi on 21 April, General Secretary Do Muoi 
cordially received the Lao People's Revolutionary Party [LPRP] 
Central Committee Organization Department delegation led by its 
chief Thongsing Thammavong currently on a visit to Vietnam. 
  Comrade Thongsing Thammavong said his delegation held 
working 
session with the Communist Party of Vietnam Central Committee 
Organization Department and other agencies concerned to exchange 
experiences and views on various issues. He said he was pleased 
to see that in the new situation the two parties, states, and 
peoples have cooperated consistently and helped each other to 
fulfill the objectives set by their respective parties. 
  General Secretary Do Muoi warmly welcomed the Lao party 
delegation and hailed the success scored by the delegation 
during the visit. He said this has further strengthened the 
close, fraternal relations between the two parties and peoples. 
  Comrade Do Muoi briefed the Lao delegation on the party 
building task in the new situation, and expressed the hope that 
both sides will continue to consistently exchange experiences 
and expand cooperation, thereby contributing to consolidating 
and developing the special friendly relations between the two 
parties and nations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

