<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Provincial, Municipal Party Delegates Visit PRC </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Provincial, Municipal Party Delegates Visit PRC </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2204021394 Hanoi VNA in English 1407 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2204021394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA April 21 -- A delegation of senior 
official of some provincial and municipal party committees of 
Vietnam led by Nguyen Tan Dung, member of the party Central 
Committee, secretary of the provincial party committee of the 
southern province of Kien Giang, made a working visit to China 
from April 9 to 19. 
  The 10-day visit was made at the invitation of the Central 
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC). 
  While in China, the delegation had working sessions with a 
delegation of the Chinese Communist Party led by Zhu Shanqing, 
deputy head of the International Liaison Department of the CPC 
Central Committee, the State Commission for Restructuring the 
Economic System. 
  It also met with the leadership of the two provinces of 
Guangdong and Hainan. The two sides exchanged views on the 
issues relating to the socio economic development in the present 
situation of each country. 
  The Vietnamese delegation also studies the renovation 
process 
in agriculture and industry in China. 

</TEXT>

