<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Tender Consideration Council Set Up </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Tender Consideration Council Set Up </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2104090694 Hanoi VNA in English 0633 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2104090694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA April 21 -- A National Tender 
Consideration Council (NTCC) has been set up to act as a 
consultative body for the prime minister in inspecting and 
evaluating the tender results of state-funded projects worth 
more than 100 billion dong (about US 10 million) or smaller ones 
decided personally by the P.M. State-funded projects include 
those using money from the state budget, bank loan, foreign aid 
and state capital in business establishments. The National 
Tender Consideration Council's duty is to organize the 
inspection and evaluation of tender results of projects from 
ministries localities and business enterprises, and then submit 
them to the prime minister, for selection. Inspection and [word 
indistinct] time is no more than 15 days after the availibility 
of all documents about tender results. Prof. Do Quoc Sam, 
minister and head of the State Planning Committee, is the NTCC 
chairman. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

